edu.unm.health.biocomp.hscaf.ScaffoldStore

Uses of ScaffoldStore in edu.unm.health.biocomp.hscaf
 

Constructors in edu.unm.health.biocomp.hscaf with parameters of type ScaffoldStore
ScaffoldTree(chemaxon.struc.Molecule mol, boolean keep_nitro_attachments, boolean stereo, ScaffoldStore scafstore)
          Create ScaffoldTree by analyzing input molecule. All scaffolds will be found and associated with the root scaffold, a.k.a. the Bemis-Murko framework. If input molecule is multi-fragment, throw exception. If scafstore is provided, it will be used as a lookup to avoid re-analysis of previously analyzed scaffolds.
